Color Theory
•	ROY G BIV: rainbow colors
•	CMYK: Printer colors – subtractive – cyan, magenta, yellow, black
•	RGB: Electronic devices - additive
•	PMS: Pantone Matching System = Spot Color
•	HEX Color: RGB 0xFFFFFF = white

Color Wheel
o	Hue (ROI G BIV)
o	Saturation: briliance – dullness (intensity)
o	Value: dark – light (light reflected)
o	Tints, pastel = Hue + white
o	Tones = Hue + grey
o	Shades = Hue + black 


